_:Ne3ed04904cc64210973624f42dcfe2e5 <http://schema.org/description> "The Armed Forces Covenant Fund Trust started work in May 2015 with £10-million per annum funding from the MOD using Libor funds. It will have distributed £50-million by the end of March 2020 supporting a range of programmes for veterans, their carers and families, serving families and supporting integration of the military and civilian communities. Armed Forces Covenant Fund Trust is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Ministry of Defence ." .
